x4freetext: Self-supporting Sn-122 and Sn-116 targets with
proportional gas counters(MWPC1,C2) for detection of
the fission fragments. These detectors contain two
planes of 162 horizontal and 156 vertical, 20 um diam.,
Two micro-channel plate Si detector assemblies
(R1,R2) were used to detect and characterize fission
light charged particles(LCP). They were set at a
distance of 19.5 cm from the target. Each telescope
was composed of three silicon counters with thicknesses
96 DEMON neutron counters each with an active
volume of 16 cm diameter and 20 cm thickness. Each
cylindrical DEMON cell is filled with NE213 liquid
Neutrons and LCP were detected in coincidence
